When: Sat Sep 29, 2012 12pm to 5pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB
Event Status: confirmed
entry.content:
When: Sat Sep 29, 2012 12pm to 5pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB
Event Status: confirmed
Event Description: Let's build some awesome hacks with the Raspberry Pi! Guests are welcome, but be advised, everyone will be laser focused on building projects for next week's event. If you'd like a tour, or want to speak to some of our members, we highly recommend stopping by at the next Open House instead. Thanks! Be sure to check our camera feed at http://twitter.com/famduino, give us a heads up on IRC, or call us on the lab's VoIP line before heading out so someone can look out for you. Things may get started earlier or later, but there will definitely be someone at the lab around noon to get things started.

entry.title: Introduction to Arduino
entry.summary:
When: Sat Oct 20, 2012 1pm to 4pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB Meeting Room
Event Status: confirmed
entry.content:
When: Sat Oct 20, 2012 1pm to 4pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB Meeting Room
Event Status: confirmed
Event Description: The Arduino platform is an amazing way to learn more about electronics or to bring your latest idea to life. In this "all ages"* beginner’s class, you will learn the basics of the Arduino hardware, and how to install and use the Arduino software. You will build simple circuits that can be controlled with the Arduino and explore “shields” that are available to expand the Arduino. Bring your own Arduino and components, or pre-order an Arduino Starter Kit which includes an Arduino Uno, a USB cable, a solderless breadboard, jumper wires, and an assortment of switches, potentiometers, LEDs and resistors. RSVP Here: http://www.eventbrite.com/event/4400602320

entry.title: Intro to Arduino
entry.summary:
When: Sat Jul 14, 2012 10am to 12pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB Meeting Room
Event Status: confirmed
entry.content:
When: Sat Jul 14, 2012 10am to 12pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB Meeting Room
Event Status: confirmed
Event Description: The Arduino platform is an amazing way to learn more about electronics or to bring your latest idea to life. In this "all ages"* beginner’s class, you will learn the basics of the Arduino hardware, and how to install and use the Arduino software. You will build simple circuits that can be controlled with the Arduino and explore “shields” that are available to expand the Arduino. Bring your own Arduino and components, or pre-order an Arduino Starter Kit which includes an Arduino Uno, a USB cable, a solderless breadboard, jumper wires, and an assortment of switches, potentiometers, LEDs and resistors. Members - FREE (does not include hardware) Non-Members - $20 (does not include hardware) Optional Arduino Starter Kit (from adafruit industries) - $45 Please Note: A personal laptop will be required to participate. If you do not purchase the Arduino Starter Kit, you will need to bring Arduino hardware to participate. Required hardware: Arduino or Arduino-compatible board, USB cable, solderless breadboard, jumper wires. If your Arduino board is not-usb powered, please bring a small power supply. *Children must be accompanied by an adult who will help faciliate the learning process. RSVP at: http://www.eventbrite.com/event/3657608004

When: Thu Jun 7, 2012 7pm to Thu Jun 7, 2012 8pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB Meeting Room
Event Status: confirmed
entry.content:
When: Thu Jun 7, 2012 7pm to Thu Jun 7, 2012 8pm  EDT

Where: FamiLAB Meeting Room
Event Status: confirmed
Event Description: If you're interested in Python, you won't want to miss the 7th June 2012 class as David Billsbrough and Steve Litt's material on "Introduction to the Python" programming language. David will delve into the benefits of using Python as well as how to write excellent Python. Steve will delve into writing object oriented Python, specifically: "How to make classes, how to instantiate objects from those classes, and a tiny bit about inheritance and "what's the deal with private variables. RSVP at: http://pythonbasics.eventbrite.com/
